<item>
            <title>[LU-15563] Support for Linux 5.16.9 server</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15563</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Linux v5.14-rc5-11-gc0891ac15f04&lt;br/&gt;
   isystem: ship and use stdarg.h&lt;br/&gt;
Change kernel includes of stdarg.h to linux/stdarg.h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux v5.14-rc6-13-g0cad6246621b&lt;br/&gt;
   vfs: add rcu argument to -&amp;gt;get_acl() callback&lt;br/&gt;
Adds an rcu argument, return -ECHILD if rcu is true.   &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux v5.15-rc1-20-g15bf32398ad4&lt;br/&gt;
   security: Return xattr name from security_dentry_init_security()&lt;br/&gt;
Adds an new argument used to return the xattr_name constant.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux v5.15-rc6-17-gfe45e630a103&lt;br/&gt;
   block: move integrity handling out of &amp;lt;linux/blkdev.h&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Include the new linux/blk-integrity.h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux v5.15-rc6-145-g6b19b766e8f0&lt;br/&gt;
   fs: get rid of the res2 iocb-&amp;gt;ki_complete argument&lt;br/&gt;
Drop the unused second &apos;res2&apos; argument.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rework the ext4_journal_get_write_access() configure test&lt;br/&gt;
to avoid a MODPOST failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rework the lock_page_memcg() configure test to avoid&lt;br/&gt;
a MODPOST failure.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
